Package examples.jmarkov

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AccessControl2Queues
    This class represents a network with 2 queues in tandem, where the second queue has a buffer of size B and the first has a unit buffer.
    BBPhase
    This is the Java implementation for the Bucket Brigades System using Phase Distribution.
    BBPhBuf
    This class is a java implementation of Bucket Brigades System using Phase Distribution and buffers among the stations.
    BBPhBufExp
    This class model a Bucket Brigades production line with phase type service times.
    BucketBrigades
    This class describes a Bucket Brigades system with no intermediate buffers, N workers and M machines with possibly uneven working velocities.
    BucketBuffers
    Model of a Bucket Brigades production system with buffers.
    DriveThru
    This class implements a Drive Thru.
    ErlangQueue
    This class implements a system with N servers with erlang services.
    HiperExQueue
    This class implements a system with one server with PH service.
    Jackson
    This class represents a "Closed Jackson Network" with numStations multi-server workstations and N entities in the system.
    Kanban
    This class implements a Kanban system with one card.
    PHLine
    This class implements a system with two tandem servers, each one with a PH service.
    PickBlockNarrow
    This class represents a Narrow Aisle Picking System with 2 pickers, n picklocs and a infinity:1 pick/walk speed ratio.
    PickBlockNarrowCont
    This class represents a Narrow Aisle Picking System with 2 pickers n picklocs and exponential picking and walking times, each time can be different for each picker.
    PickBlockNarrowSlow
    This class represents a Narrow Aisle Picking System with 2 pickers n picklocs and a 1:1 pick/walk speed ratio.
    PickBlockWide
    This class represents a Wide Aisle Picking System with 2 pickers n picklocs and a infinity:1 pick/walk speed ratio.
    PickBlockWideContKPickers_V3
    This class represents a Wide Aisle Picking System with 2 pickers n picklocs and exponential picking and walking times, each time is different for each picker.
    PickBlockWideSlow
    This class represents a Wide Aisle Picking System with 2 pickers n picklocs and a 1:1 pick/walk speed ratio.
    QueueMEk1
    This example represents a queueing system with Poisson arrivals at rate lambda' if the system is empty, and a rate lambda otherwise.
    QueueMH2k1
    This example represents a queueing system with Poisson arrivals at rate $\lambda’$ if the system is empty, and a rate $\lambda$ otherwise.
    QueueMM1N
    This class implements an M/M/1/N queue.
    QueueMM2dN
    This class represents a system with 2 different exponential servers with rates mu1 and mu2, respectively, and arrival rate lambda.
    QueueMMKdN
    This class represents is a system with K different exponential servers with rates mu1, mu2, etc, respectively, and arrival rate lambda.
    QueuePhPh2
    This class implements a system whit two tandem servers each one with a phase service.
    Web
    This is an example of a web server that can receive different M types of items and can serve N simultaneous items with a maximum queue capacity of MaxQueue.
